name: ExtensionBodyStructure_IncludedStructure
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.BodyStructure.includedStructure` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `BodyStructure.includedStructure` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `BodyStructure.includedStructure` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`BodyStructure.includedStructure` 1..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `BodyStructure.includedStructure` 1..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `BodyStructure` 0..* `BodyStructure`
*  R4: `BodyStructure` 0..* `BodyStructure`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `BodyStructure.includedStructure` is mapped to FHIR R4 element `BodyStructure` as `SourceIsNarrowerThanTarget`, concept domain: `NotRelatedTo`, value domain: `NotRelatedTo`.
